# Conventional Commits

All commits use **Conventional Commits** enforced by Commitlint (`commitlint.config.cjs`).

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body — use this when detail does not fit the header rule]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- **scope** (optional): short area, e.g. `ui`, `router`, `deps`
- **description** (required): imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end

## Header length (strict)

- The **entire first line** (from `feat` through the end of the description) must be **at most 100 characters** (`header-max-length`).
- Prefer **short** subjects (~50–72 chars). If you need more detail, add a **blank line** and a **body**; do not cram everything into the first line.

## Examples (valid headers)

```
feat(ui): add shadcn button and app shell layout
fix(router): correct dashboard lazy route
chore(deps): bump angular patch version
```

## Example when detail is long (use body)

**Bad** (header too long; will fail Commitlint):

```
feat(ui): implement button component with variants and size options; enhance app layout with theme service and routing
```

**Good**:

```
feat(ui): add button variants and app shell with theme

- UbButton directive and layout shell
- ThemeService, routes for home/dashboard/forms
```

## Anti-patterns

- First line longer than 100 characters
- `WIP`, `fix stuff`, or vague one-word subjects
- Subject line ending with `.`
- Type not in the allowed list

## When suggesting a commit for the user

1. Propose a **header** that satisfies **type**, **scope**, and **≤ 100 characters** total on line 1.
2. If more context is needed, add a **body** after one blank line (bullet or short paragraphs).
3. Do not output a single overloaded line that exceeds the limit.
